gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 140, Spurs 114
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder won their fourth consecutive game as they defeated the Spurs, 140-114. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the Thunder with his 32nd 30-point game of the year, with 32 points (12-12 FT), six rebounds, 10 assists as Chet Holmgren added 17 points, nine rebounds, three blocks, and four assists. Victor Wembanyama led the Spurs with 24 points, 12 rebounds, and four blocks as Devin Vassell added 21 points, five rebounds, and seven assists. The Thunder improve to 31-13 as the Spurs move to 8-36.
